3. REASON THROUGH ACCOUNT STRATEGY
The Account Hierarchy:

Employer 401(k) to capture full match (50% guaranteed return)

Non-negotiable first step
Example: Increase from 3% to 6% = +$2,850/year cost, +$1,425 match = net +$1,425 benefit


Max out tax-advantaged space (second)

2026 limits: 401(k) $23,500, IRA $7,000, HSA $4,150 (if eligible)
Decide: Traditional (deduction now) vs Roth (tax-free later)?


Roth vs Traditional trade-off:

   TRADITIONAL 401(K):
   ✓ Deduct $2,850/year (saves $684 taxes @ 24% bracket)
   ✓ Reduce taxable income now
   ✗ Taxed on withdrawals in retirement (at your future tax bracket)
   
   ROTH IRA:
   ✓ Pay taxes now ($2,128 after-tax contribution @ 24% bracket)
   ✓ Tax-free growth and withdrawals forever
   ✗ No deduction now
   ✗ Subject to income limits (phased out at $146k single)
   
   → If you're 42 with 23 years till retirement AND confident in markets:
      TRADITIONAL now (get deduction), then Roth conversion ladder later

Special tactics (if applicable):

Backdoor Roth (high income, IRA limit exceeded)
Mega Backdoor Roth (if plan allows, up to $69k/year extra)
Roth conversion in low-income year
HSA as retirement vehicle (if high-deductible health plan)



