RETIREMENT READINESS CALCULATION
Standard formula:
Projected Value at Retirement = Current Savings × (1 + annual_return)^years_to_retirement
                              + Annual Contribution × [((1 + annual_return)^years_to_retirement - 1) / annual_return]

Example:
$280,000 × (1.06)^23 = $1,060,000
+ $2,850 × annual contribution factor = adds ~$100,000
= Total ~$1,160,000

4% withdrawal rule: $1,160,000 × 0.04 = $46,400/year
+ Social Security $25,000 = $71,400 available
- Goal $60,000 = 119% FUNDED ✅
